[
  {
    "text": "♪ Mellow instrumental hip-hop ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "Manda Paul: Hi, my name is Manda. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=10"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm on the Apple Vision Science team ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=13"
  },
  {
    "text": "Herman Damveld: And I am Herman, and I'm a research scientist ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "here at Apple. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "Creating experiences in three dimensions makes use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "of unique modalities such as depth and full field of view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "We will introduce you to how a person may experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "this new level of immersion through visual cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=28"
  },
  {
    "text": "and motion information from 3D content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=30"
  },
  {
    "text": "and where human limitations may interfere ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=33"
  },
  {
    "text": "with comfort of people experiencing your apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "Manda: Our guidelines are to help you create experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are comfortable and enjoyable. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll talk through visual depth cues, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=46"
  },
  {
    "text": "content parameters, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "eye effort, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "motion of virtual objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=53"
  },
  {
    "text": "head-locked content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "motion in windows, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "and oscillating motion. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "To begin, it's important that your content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=63"
  },
  {
    "text": "provides correct visual depth cues to the viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "This matters because well-designed 3D content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "enables the brain to perceive depth. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, a bit of science. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "We have multiple sensory systems ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "with which we experience the real ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "and virtual world. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "At the very high level, the visual system is responsible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "for taking in light from the content you create ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "and interpreting it into what is perceived. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=93"
  },
  {
    "text": "That is to say, your design decisions ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "have a significant impact on vision comfort for your viewers. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "Agreement between the depth intended by you ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=104"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the depth perceived by the viewer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=108"
  },
  {
    "text": "is necessary for vision comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=110"
  },
  {
    "text": "As an image moves in depth, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "the brain enlists the eye muscles to converge ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=117"
  },
  {
    "text": "the line of sight and fixate the eyes at the image depth. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "This enables a single image to be perceived. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "To converge the eyes correctly, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "the brain needs correct visual depth cues. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=131"
  },
  {
    "text": "Vision comfort might be affected when depth cues are missing, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "conflicting, or misleading. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "The viewer might experience discomforts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as double vision or eye fatigue. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=143"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's see how we can use image cues to maintain vision comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=146"
  },
  {
    "text": "When working with scenes that are very sparse, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "as in this image of a citrus, many visual cues are missing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=154"
  },
  {
    "text": "that might have conveyed depth information. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "The brain might be unable to reconcile what depth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "to converge the eyes to, hence causing discomfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "Seeing the color of the citrus enables the familiar size cue. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "If the slice looks green, the brain uses the prior knowledge ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the size of a lime to inform what depth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=179"
  },
  {
    "text": "this slice might be floating at ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "and converges the eyes at that correct depth. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=184"
  },
  {
    "text": "Using blur is another way to convey depth information. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "Relative size can also be used ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "to add depth cues to a sparse image. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "The larger of the two slices from the lime ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "is perceived to be closer to the viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=202"
  },
  {
    "text": "Gentle motion can also provide a reference ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=206"
  },
  {
    "text": "for what depth the line of sight should point to. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "My colleague Herman, will elaborate on the nuances ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "of using motion in your content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "For now, let's add just a few more cues to direct the eyes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "An added background, light and shadow, occlusion, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "and texture density are some more methods ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "to add in the missing visual depth cues. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "Conflicting cues are also troublesome. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=233"
  },
  {
    "text": "As mentioned, the bottom slice appears closer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "since it looks larger. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "We expect it to be in front ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "and occlude the smaller looking slice. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=242"
  },
  {
    "text": "However here, relative size cue conflicts with occlusion cue, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "telling the brain the opposite of what we expect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "The conflict between the depth cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=253"
  },
  {
    "text": "might lead to vision discomfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "Conflicting cues are not unique to sparse scenes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "The more conflict there is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "the more challenging for vision comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=264"
  },
  {
    "text": "So, ensure all of the depth cues from your content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "give the brain correct information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=273"
  },
  {
    "text": "so to align the viewer's eyes to the depth you intended. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=275"
  },
  {
    "text": "One more thought about depth is correcting the visual cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=280"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are misleading, such as repeating patterns. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=282"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here, both eyes are pointed to the same object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the repeating pattern. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's great! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=291"
  },
  {
    "text": "However here, each eye locks onto a different object ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the repeating pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=297"
  },
  {
    "text": "and when the brain tries to combine the images ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=299"
  },
  {
    "text": "from each eye into one, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=301"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's perceived at a different depth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=303"
  },
  {
    "text": "than the repeating pattern is intended to be. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "To mitigate this conflict and to avoid double vision, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=309"
  },
  {
    "text": "use smaller portions of the pattern ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=312"
  },
  {
    "text": "or break up the pattern with another design. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=315"
  },
  {
    "text": "A final note about depth perception. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=320"
  },
  {
    "text": "The 3D content, along with your visual depth cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "will automatically be rendered on each display ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=326"
  },
  {
    "text": "per eye appropriately to enable someone to see ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "the depth you intended. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=332"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you choose to manually render stereo content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "for stereo video, for example, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=338"
  },
  {
    "text": "it is extremely important to not only have correct depth cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "but also have correct disparity for each eye ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=344"
  },
  {
    "text": "so to avoid extremely conflicting visual cues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "which could lead to severe vision discomfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=350"
  },
  {
    "text": "All right! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's move on to content parameters ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=355"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as size and contrast. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=357"
  },
  {
    "text": "Visually comfortable content have parameters suited ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=360"
  },
  {
    "text": "for each specific visual experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=364"
  },
  {
    "text": "Choose parameters that reduce visual effort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=366"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here are some scenarios. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=370"
  },
  {
    "text": "Content requiring fixating the eyes for an extended time, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=373"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as for reading, is most visually comfortable ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "when placed farther than arm's-length distance. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "In addition, enable a person to adjust content depth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=384"
  },
  {
    "text": "so they may choose a depth that's most comfortable for them ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=388"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "Reserve content closest to the viewer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "for experiences demanding only momentary visual effort ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=396"
  },
  {
    "text": "or for experiences inviting direct interaction ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=400"
  },
  {
    "text": "which occurs when someone's hand actually intersects an item ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "in 3D space. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "Otherwise, you may use visual cues, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=410"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as transparency or blur, to redirect eyes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "to a farther depth to increase visual comfort.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=417"
  },
  {
    "text": "Similar to depth, content size and contrast ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=424"
  },
  {
    "text": "should match the particular visual experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=427"
  },
  {
    "text": "you are designing to allow for vision comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, utilize higher contrast for reading text ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=434"
  },
  {
    "text": "and lower contrast, transparency, or blur ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=438"
  },
  {
    "text": "to redirect visual attention elsewhere. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "Choose text size and window size and depth ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "for extended reading such that text is legible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "with comfortable eye scanning, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=453"
  },
  {
    "text": "without the need to rotate the head or body. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=455"
  },
  {
    "text": "One more parameter to be mindful of is content brightness. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=459"
  },
  {
    "text": "When a large portion of the field of view is dark ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=463"
  },
  {
    "text": "as in this image, slow down the transition ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=466"
  },
  {
    "text": "to a bright scene to give time to the eye ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=470"
  },
  {
    "text": "for brightness adaptation and ensure vision comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "One last thing to be mindful of for vision comfort ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the effort required from the eyes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=481"
  },
  {
    "text": "For a more comfortable visual experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "minimize eye effort demanded from your viewers. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is how. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=489"
  },
  {
    "text": "When choosing content location, keep in mind ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=491"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's most comfortable for people to turn their eyes downwards ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "or left and right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=499"
  },
  {
    "text": "So choose those positions for your content when possible. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=501"
  },
  {
    "text": "Upward and diagonal eye rotation requires most eye-muscle effort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "Holding the eyes at those positions can be fatiguing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "Content requiring extended reading ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=515"
  },
  {
    "text": "or elongated target fixations should be placed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=518"
  },
  {
    "text": "towards the center and slightly below line of sight ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=521"
  },
  {
    "text": "to provide a comfortable visual experience. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=524"
  },
  {
    "text": "If extreme eye-rotation angles are necessary ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "for your experience, design for brief interactions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=531"
  },
  {
    "text": "or else move them to the center of field of view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=535"
  },
  {
    "text": "to reduce eye-rotation effort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=538"
  },
  {
    "text": "It is also important to consider that a person might prefer ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=542"
  },
  {
    "text": "to take a break to rest their eyes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=545"
  },
  {
    "text": "To enable this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=548"
  },
  {
    "text": "design for natural break points in your experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=549"
  },
  {
    "text": "to allow for the person's eyes to rest. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=552"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's it for vision comfort! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=557"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, my colleague Herman will walk you through ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=559"
  },
  {
    "text": "how to design apps for motion comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=561"
  },
  {
    "text": "Herman: Thanks, Manda! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=564"
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we are going to have a look ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=565"
  },
  {
    "text": "at how the motion information from content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=567"
  },
  {
    "text": "in your immersive apps can affect a person's experience ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=569"
  },
  {
    "text": "and where human limitations may interfere with comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's start with digging a little further into the science. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=576"
  },
  {
    "text": "We, human beings, use multiple sensory systems ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=581"
  },
  {
    "text": "to experience the real and virtual world. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=584"
  },
  {
    "text": "We already saw that the visual system is responsible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=588"
  },
  {
    "text": "for taking in light and interpreting what is perceived. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=591"
  },
  {
    "text": "Part of that perception is your own motion. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "The vestibular system in your inner ear ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=599"
  },
  {
    "text": "also measures your own movements. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=602"
  },
  {
    "text": "Normally, the visual motion information ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=606"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the motion that you perceive with your vestibular system ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=608"
  },
  {
    "text": "are always in agreement. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "But when the visual motion information is missing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=615"
  },
  {
    "text": "or conflicting with the vestibular information, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=617"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can experience motion discomfort, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=620"
  },
  {
    "text": "such as dizziness or an upset stomach. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=622"
  },
  {
    "text": "Well-designed content enables the brain ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "to perceive the world as stationary. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=628"
  },
  {
    "text": "This provides a sense of stability ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=630"
  },
  {
    "text": "and is necessary for motion comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=633"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's go over some scenarios with motion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=636"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see how we can maintain motion comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first scenario deals with motion of virtual objects. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=641"
  },
  {
    "text": "When one or more virtual objects, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=647"
  },
  {
    "text": "like these blue polyhedrons here, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=649"
  },
  {
    "text": "cover a large part of the field of view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=650"
  },
  {
    "text": "and move, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=653"
  },
  {
    "text": "the viewer's brain might interpret the visual motion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=656"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the objects as if the viewer themself is moving. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=658"
  },
  {
    "text": "This upsets the sense of stability ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=662"
  },
  {
    "text": "and can cause motion discomfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=664"
  },
  {
    "text": "As a designer, you can mitigate this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=667"
  },
  {
    "text": "by making objects semitransparent when they move, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=669"
  },
  {
    "text": "so the passthrough content is clearly visible ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=672"
  },
  {
    "text": "during the motion. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=675"
  },
  {
    "text": "Whenever possible, avoid using head-locked content. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=678"
  },
  {
    "text": "That is content that is anchored to the user's head. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=683"
  },
  {
    "text": "Head-locked content will be, always, in the same position ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=688"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the field of view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=691"
  },
  {
    "text": "If head-locked views are necessary, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=693"
  },
  {
    "text": "use a smaller window size ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=695"
  },
  {
    "text": "placed near the center of the line of sight ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=697"
  },
  {
    "text": "and farther away from the viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "Whenever possible, use world-locked views ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=702"
  },
  {
    "text": "to prevent content from feeling stuck. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=705"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another alternative is to use a lazy-follow animation. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "This moves content slowly towards a destination over time. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=712"
  },
  {
    "text": "You also want to be mindful of the motion of the content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=718"
  },
  {
    "text": "that will be visible in a virtual window. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=721"
  },
  {
    "text": "When the content in a window, such as this virtual landscape, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=725"
  },
  {
    "text": "moves...",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=728"
  },
  {
    "text": "...the viewer's brain might interpret the visual motion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=734"
  },
  {
    "text": "as if the viewer themself is moving.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=737"
  },
  {
    "text": "To provide optimal motion comfort, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=742"
  },
  {
    "text": "you want to be mindful about camera motions. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=744"
  },
  {
    "text": "For starters, keep the horizon of the content in the window ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=747"
  },
  {
    "text": "aligned with the real horizon. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=750"
  },
  {
    "text": "The point where all the pixels appear to be coming from ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=754"
  },
  {
    "text": "is called the focus of expansion. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=757"
  },
  {
    "text": "That's where you're going, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=760"
  },
  {
    "text": "and people have a natural tendency to look at that point. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=762"
  },
  {
    "text": "You want to move the camera in such a way ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=766"
  },
  {
    "text": "that the motion of the focus of expansion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=768"
  },
  {
    "text": "is slow and predictable, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you want to keep the focus of expansion ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=773"
  },
  {
    "text": "within the field of view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=775"
  },
  {
    "text": "That means that you want to avoid fast turns ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=778"
  },
  {
    "text": "or pure rotational motion. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=781"
  },
  {
    "text": "The focus of expansion shifts ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=784"
  },
  {
    "text": "out of the field of view in those cases. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=786"
  },
  {
    "text": "As an alternative to fast rotations, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=789"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use instantaneous directional changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=791"
  },
  {
    "text": "during a quick fade-out. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=794"
  },
  {
    "text": "To optimize for motion comfort, you also want to avoid ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=797"
  },
  {
    "text": "that large objects shoot by at close range, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=801"
  },
  {
    "text": "as seen here on the right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=804"
  },
  {
    "text": "Best keep objects small and at a larger distance, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=807"
  },
  {
    "text": "as on the left. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=811"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if possible, use plain textures ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=814"
  },
  {
    "text": "with low luminance contrast, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=816"
  },
  {
    "text": "which makes the motion less perceivable by your eyes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=818"
  },
  {
    "text": "The last type of motion scenario to be mindful of ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=823"
  },
  {
    "text": "deals with sustained oscillations of objects ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=826"
  },
  {
    "text": "and animations. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=828"
  },
  {
    "text": "To ensure a comfortable experience, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=831"
  },
  {
    "text": "try to avoid oscillations in general, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=834"
  },
  {
    "text": "and in particular those with frequencies around 0.2 Hz. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=836"
  },
  {
    "text": "That is one oscillation per 5 seconds. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=840"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if you really cannot avoid showing oscillating motions, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=846"
  },
  {
    "text": "try to keep the amplitude of the motion low ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=849"
  },
  {
    "text": "and make the content semitransparent. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=853"
  },
  {
    "text": "This makes the motion much less perceivable by your eyes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=856"
  },
  {
    "text": "as seen on the left. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=859"
  },
  {
    "text": "And it's always a good idea ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=861"
  },
  {
    "text": "to provide an oscillation-free alternative ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=862"
  },
  {
    "text": "through the Reduce Motion accessibility setting. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=864"
  },
  {
    "text": "To wrap it up, here's a summary of the things to keep in mind ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=869"
  },
  {
    "text": "when designing for motion comfort. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=872"
  },
  {
    "text": "Try to provide a sense of stability, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=875"
  },
  {
    "text": "avoid head-locked content, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=878"
  },
  {
    "text": "be gentle with camera motion, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=880"
  },
  {
    "text": "and avoid oscillations if you can. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=882"
  },
  {
    "text": "To learn more about principles of spatial design ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=885"
  },
  {
    "text": "and see many of our vision and motion guidelines in action, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=888"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can recommend visiting the sessions listed here. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=891"
  },
  {
    "text": "Manda: That's it for us. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=895"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can't wait to see what amazing experiences ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=897"
  },
  {
    "text": "you will create! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=899"
  },
  {
    "text": "Herman: Thank you for watching! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=901"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2023/10078/?time=902"
  }
]